article.headline: CS Bakersfield 63, Sacramento St. 60
article.story: BAKERSFIELD, Calif. -- Tyrone White scored 12 points, all on 3-pointers, and Cal State Bakersfield held on to beat Sacramento State 63-60 Wednesday night. White accounted for half of the Roadrunners' 3-pointers, going 4 for 7 from behind the arc. Bakersfield (5-2) also got 11 points from Zach Lamb, and Rashad Savage grabbed 14 rebounds. The Roadrunners raced to a 33-17 halftime lead, and built the margin to 21 points before Sacramento State rallied. The Hornets had a chance to tie in the final seconds but missed on a 3-point attempt. John Dickson finished with 19 points for the Hornets (3-5). Heath Hoffman scored 11 and added seven rebounds.
